Allied Technologies, Brait and Harmony: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-05-04T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/allied-technologies-brait-and-harmony-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are from
the last close. The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index fell to the
lowest level since April 19, losing 469.19, or 1.5 percent, to
31,856.64 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Allied Technologies Ltd. (ALT)  : The maker of television
set-top boxes was upgraded to “buy” from “hold” by analysts
Religare Capital Markets Ltd. Analyst Craig Hackney increased
his price estimate on the stock to 73 rand, from 63 rand. The
share closed 2 cents higher at 63.85 rand.  Brait SA (BAT)  : South Africa’s biggest private equity
company said in a statement that shareholders approved its
proposed 6 billion rand ($901 million) restructuring and
purchase of additional stakes in Pepkor Holdings Ltd. and
Premier Foods Group Ltd. with a 99.4 percent majority at an
extra-ordinary  shareholders’ meeting  yesterday. The stock rose
11 cents, or 0.6 percent, to 18.80 rand.  Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HAR SJ): Africa’s third-largest
producer of the metal releases earnings for the quarter through
March. The stock declined 3 rand, or 3.1 percent, to 94 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
